[test strategy]
# gen105 (L20): reasoning about its OWN strategy. gen78 could name which module
# answered; L20 answers the CONTROL question — "why did you answer that way?" —
# from the real execution trace the dispatcher recorded: the modules actually
# consulted that declined, the one that claimed the turn, and the first-match-wins
# rule that explains why the rest were never reached. Derived from real runtime
# state, never a confabulated story (PRINCIPLES.md, the reflexive closure).

# Before any substantive turn, there is no decision to explain — say so honestly.
> why did you answer that way?
< I haven't answered anything substantive yet, so there's no decision to explain.

# A substantive turn: few-shot induction claims it.
> cat -> cats, dog -> dogs, bird -> ?
< birds.
# Now the meta-question. The trace is REAL: memory/meta/role/self genuinely ran
# and declined this turn before fewshot claimed it; the rest were never consulted.
> why did you answer that way?
< I try my modules in a fixed order and the first one that matches wins. Last turn initiative, piact, compose, repair, input, gen, deepreason, count, namestart, sequence, spell, world, translate, synth, induce, verify, memory, loop, meta, counterfactual, whatifnot, robust, calibrate, abduce, role, self, archetype looked first and declined; then 'fewshot' claimed it — so the modules after 'fewshot' were never consulted.

# Asking again does NOT change the answer: the introspective turn does not
# overwrite the trace it reports (it reasons about the decision, not its own lookup).
> why did you answer that way?
< I try my modules in a fixed order and the first one that matches wins. Last turn initiative, piact, compose, repair, input, gen, deepreason, count, namestart, sequence, spell, world, translate, synth, induce, verify, memory, loop, meta, counterfactual, whatifnot, robust, calibrate, abduce, role, self, archetype looked first and declined; then 'fewshot' claimed it — so the modules after 'fewshot' were never consulted.

# The fallback case is explained just as honestly: every module looked and declined.
> xyzzy plugh
< I don't understand that yet.
> why did you answer that way?
< I try my modules in a fixed order and the first one that matches wins. Last turn initiative, piact, compose, repair, input, gen, deepreason, count, namestart, sequence, spell, world, translate, synth, induce, verify, memory, loop, meta, counterfactual, whatifnot, robust, calibrate, abduce, role, self, archetype, fewshot, compare, rulespec, algebra, arith, plan, wordproblem, agent, search, tool, quantity, cause, same, analogy, conj, coref, bench, reader, shell, answerframe, aggregate, codeast, code, knowledge, symbolic, summary, discourse, pragma, family, personal, social, chitchat, reqgen, learn, toolpolicy, smalltalk each looked and declined, and nothing else claimed it, so I fell back to an honest "I don't understand."
